      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must be documented and traceable to CPB operating envelope; blood analog fluid properties must be specified within ±5% of physiological values.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments conducted using 37% glycerol-water blood analog (viscosity 3.5 cP at 37°C, within 3.2% of target). Flow rates and rotational speeds verified with calibrated Coriolis flowmeter and optical tachometer. Temperature controlled to 37±0.5°C throughout testing."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted NIH values must agree with experimental measurements within 15% mean absolute error across all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute error in NIH predictions = 8.3% across five operating points from three independent laboratories. Maximum single-point error = 12.7% at 6 L/min, 2500 RPM. All predictions within acceptance band. Relative hemolysis index RH = 0.87 at worst-case condition, satisfying RH < 1 criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
