      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantities of interest (NIH, RH index) must be directly linked to clinical hemolysis endpoints and regulatory acceptance criteria.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is the FDA-recognized metric for pump hemolysis assessment. Relative hemolysis index RH directly compares device performance to predicate, consistent with 510(k) substantial equivalence pathway. Both QoIs are mechanistically linked to red blood cell lysis via shear stress exposure time integration."
    },
